    {
      "repo": "sg-evals/kubernetes-client-go",
      "path": "kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go",
      "symbol": "DeploymentInterface.Create",
      "description": "Client-side interface method that initiates Deployment creation. The deployments struct implements this by calling the underlying RESTClient to send an HTTP POST request to the API server."
    },
    {
      "repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes",
      "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/create.go",
      "symbol": "createHandler",
      "description": "HTTP request handler on the API server that receives the POST request for Deployment creation. It deserializes the request body, performs validation, and calls Create on the storage REST interface."
    },
    {
      "repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes",
      "path": "pkg/registry/apps/deployment/storage/storage.go",
      "symbol": "REST.Create",
      "description": "REST storage implementation for Deployments. The REST struct wraps genericregistry.Store and delegates Create operations to the underlying storage backend, handling Deployment-specific validation and strategy."
    },
    {
      "repo": "kubernetes/kubernetes",
      "path": "staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/store.go",
      "symbol": "store.Create",
      "description": "etcd3 storage backend implementation that encodes the Deployment object and persists it to etcd. It handles serialization, lease attachment, and error conversion."
    },
    {
      "repo": "etcd-io-etcd",
      "path": "server/mvcc/kv.go",
      "symbol": "WriteView.Put",
      "description": "KV store interface method that performs the actual key-value write operation. The Put method is part of the WriteView interface which all write transactions must implement."
    },
    {
      "repo": "etcd-io-etcd",
      "path": "server/mvcc/kvstore.go",
      "symbol": "store",
      "description": "MVCC key-value store implementation in etcd that manages versioned key-value pairs, transactions, and the underlying backend storage via BoltDB."
    }
  ],
  "text": "When a Kubernetes client application creates a Deployment, the request flows through three distinct layers:\n\n**CLIENT LAYER (kubernetes-client-go):**\nThe process begins in the kubernetes-client-go library. An application calls the `Create()` method on a `DeploymentInterface` object (defined in `kubernetes/typed/apps/v1/deployment.go`). This interface is implemented by the `deployments` struct, which wraps `gentype.ClientWithListAndApply`. The Create method constructs an HTTP POST request containing the serialized Deployment manifest and sends it to the API server's REST endpoint.\n\n**API SERVER LAYER (kubernetes-kubernetes):**\nThe HTTP POST request arrives at the Kubernetes API server, where it is routed to the `createHandler` function in `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/endpoints/handlers/create.go`. This handler:\n1. Extracts the namespace and object name from the request\n2. Deserializes the request body into a Deployment object\n3. Performs admission control checks\n4. Calls the `Create()` method on a `rest.Creater` implementation\n\nFor Deployments, the Creater is the `REST` struct defined in `pkg/registry/apps/deployment/storage/storage.go`. This REST storage implementation wraps `genericregistry.Store` and applies Deployment-specific validation strategies. The Store ultimately calls through to the etcd3 storage backend via `staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/store.go`, where the `store.Create()` function serializes the Deployment object (typically as JSON or protobuf) and prepares it for persistence.\n\n**STORAGE LAYER (etcd-io-etcd):**\nThe serialized Deployment is passed to etcd's key-value store implementation. The etcd3 backend interfaces with the MVCC (Multi-Version Concurrency Control) engine defined in `server/mvcc/kvstore.go`. A write transaction is created (implementing the `TxnWrite` interface from `server/mvcc/kv.go`), and the serialized Deployment is written to the key-value store via the `Put()` method defined in the `WriteView` interface. \n\nThe `Put()` method in `server/mvcc/kvstore.go` performs the actual write operation, allocating a new revision number, updating the in-memory index, and persisting the key-value pair to the underlying BoltDB backend. The transaction is then committed, making the Deployment object durable and visible to all future read operations.\n\n**Summary:**\nThe complete flow is: client application → kubernetes-client-go REST Client → API server HTTP handler → DeploymentInterface.Create() → REST storage Create() → etcd3 store.Create() → etcd MVCC store Put() → persistent storage (BoltDB). Each layer adds validation, transformation, and durability guarantees, ensuring that the Deployment specification is accurately stored and can be retrieved by controllers and other clients."
}

